 I get more intelligent questions about audio, and video ITC on non EVP
=
groups, than I have ever gotten from these EVP groups. I get a much
better =
discussion going if I go to various &quot;new age&quot; groups, and get
away from the=
 EVP groups. To me, not wanting to sound negative, and I am
guilty too, but=
 it seems everyone is so intent on sharing, and
presenting what they get it=
 becomes a contest of egos. I think the
concept, and reality of EVP has pre=
tty much been proven, except to the
idiot skeptics and debunkers that would=
 tell lies to have people believe
other wise. I think the work now should s=
hift to improving the
communications, which is the purpose of ITC. I don&#39;t =
concern myself with
why spirits are hanging around grave yards and haunted =
houses, anymore
than I would want to go investigate why homeless people han=
g around bus
stations and under bridges. Yes there are intelligent people t=
here, and
you can get some witty conversation, but I don&#39;t have time that. =
I want
something consistent, and predictable. 



 It&#39;s unfortunate that t=
oo many find it easier to believe that my voices
are assembled by myself, t=
han to try to the system, or anything similar,
like EVPmaker. I have yet to=
 hear of anyone building my circuits the way
they are presented on my site,=
 yet many will claim they know how it
works, or in most cases, how it does =
not work. I would love to see some
debunker out there assemble one of these=
 voices with a coherent message,
forward and reverse. Take this voice about=
 my son&#39;s hand injury a couple
years ago, you can play the first part in re=
verse, &quot;Chad&#39;s fingers
fucked up&quot; in reveres, and get &quot;an accident makes th=
is&quot;. I challenge
anyone to tell me how the hell you can assemble a voice to=
 get a
meaningful message forward and reverse! Of course the debunkers will=

tell that&#39;s easy, cuz there is no reverse speech. 



 It seems to me tha=
t this debunking ploy saying my voices are faked is
spreading among researc=
hes, and it easier to accept this lying BS, than
to try mine, or any other =
methods. It&#39;s tempting to withdraw from any
groups. 



 Frank


